Public sector. Public services. Stakeholders in the context of public service development. Public services design. Co-operation and service co-creation with private sector and non-governmental organisations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Subject gives overview of how public sector functions, course outlines the main model how to develop public services and how public service development differs from private sector service development. The course also gives an overview about the possibilities for public sector to cooperate and co-create the services with private sector and nongovernmental sector.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the fundamental principles of public sector and its impact on public services and service development; 2) understands the special properties of service development in public sector; 3) knows the principles of developing public services in co-operatio with other public, private and non-governmental organisations; 4) is able to develop public services.
